<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Our business</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
Corporate Audit is responsible for performing independent reviews and tests to ensure that appropriate controls over risk are in place and functioning properly throughout Bank of America. The department covers all areas of the Company and performs reviews based upon assessments of items deemed to be of higher risk.
<br><br>
The group regularly provides management and the Board of Directors with a thorough and independent assessment of the Company's risk management systems and internal controls. Additionally, Corporate Audit provides risk-based advice and counsel to management to help develop and maintain an appropriate customer-focused risk management culture that supports the Company's business objectives.
</p>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Qualifications</h2>
<ul class="prp">
	<li>Pursuing a Bachelor's or Master's degree in Accounting, Finance, Computer Sciences, or General Business</li>
	<li>Grade point average of at least 3.25 on a 4 point scale</li>
	<li>Strong verbal and written communication skills</li>
	<li>Knowledge of statistics, risk management, and/or Six Sigma (or other quality programs) is desirable</li>
	<li>Successful candidates will possess a positive attitude, flexibility, open mindedness, decisiveness, and a commitment to do what it takes to get the job done</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Training</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
New hires to Corporate Audit experience a multi-phase training process that begins with a robust 8-module, web-based training program that covers basic risk concepts and the Bank of America audit process. The web-based training is followed by a multi-day instructor-led training class where the associate gains hands-on experience practicing the audit process and tools. Following classroom training, the new auditor is placed on an audit team, with an experienced peer coach and manager who provide on-the-job coaching around the day-to-day execution of the audit process.
</p>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
In addition to the training and coaching for new associates, the department provides training opportunities for more experienced auditors, audit managers and directors to support their roles within the audit process throughout their careers. This includes classroom training specific to the audit process as well as training on skills such as leadership, critical thinking, communication, management, delegation, team building and negotiation.
</p>

